Reasoning: The paper reports on an empirical cognitive study that investigates how humans evaluate arguments in complex argumentation frameworks. The study involves natural language arguments and graphical depictions of the attack relation between them, which suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves human participants, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the study involves the evaluation of argumentation semantics, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
